  "texts": [
    "BioBERT and BioClinicalBERT only correctly labelled one free text term containing 'calculi' as 'No Malignancy'.",
    "In this work, we have presented five compact clinical transformers that have achieved significant improvement over their baselines on a variety of clinical text-mining tasks.",
    "To train our models, we utilised both continual learning and knowledge distillation techniques.",
    "For continual learning, we employed the BioDistilBERT and BioMobileBERT models, which are compact models derived using standard techniques and trained on large biomedical data.",
    "Our experiments showed that the average performance of these models can increase by up to 2% after training on the MIMIC-III clinical notes dataset, and they even outperformed larger baselines on the i2b2-2010 and ICN datasets (Table 4)."
